BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 190.40 Tm (Almost every object needs other objects to do its job - a controller needs a service, a service) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 175.40 Tm (needs a repository. The question is: who creates those collaborators? Dependency Injection says) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 160.40 Tm (an object should not create its own collaborators. Instead they're created elsewhere and injected -) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 145.40 Tm (handed in - from outside. Why is that better? Looser coupling - a class depends on what it needs,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 130.40 Tm (not on how that thing is built. Easier testing - in a test you can inject a fake or mock instead of the) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 115.40 Tm (real thing. Less plumbing - Spring's container creates the objects and supplies them automatically.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 100.40 Tm (And single responsibility - a class focuses on its own job, not on managing its dependencies') Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 85.40 Tm (lifecycles.) Tj ET
