BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 754.00 Tm (SAY \(read aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 738.00 Tm (REST - Representational State Transfer - is the dominant architectural style for web APIs. The) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 723.00 Tm (core idea is to model your application as a set of resources - nouns - each addressable by a URL,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 708.00 Tm (and to act on them using the standard HTTP methods - verbs. A resource is a thing: a user, an) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 693.00 Tm (order, a greeting. It lives at a URL like slash-users-slash-42. You act on it with a verb - GET to) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 678.00 Tm (read, POST to create, PUT to update, DELETE to remove. Each request is stateless - it carries) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 663.00 Tm (everything the server needs, so the server keeps no memory of previous requests, which is what) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 648.00 Tm (makes REST easy to scale. Responses are usually JSON, though today we'll return plain text to) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 633.00 Tm (keep our first example simple.) Tj ET
0.040 0.520 1.000 rg 58.00 618.00 3.00 142.00 re f
