BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 515.50 Tm (Every interaction with a REST API uses an HTTP method that expresses intent, and Spring gives) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 500.50 Tm (each verb a dedicated annotation that maps a URL to one of your Java methods. GET reads data) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 485.50 Tm (and is safe - it makes no changes - and maps to at-GetMapping. POST creates new data,) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 470.50 Tm (at-PostMapping. PUT updates or replaces, at-PutMapping. DELETE removes, at-DeleteMapping.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 455.50 Tm (Choosing the right verb is part of designing a clean API - for instance, a GET must never modify) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 440.50 Tm (data, so it's safe to retry or cache. Today's lab uses only at-GetMapping, because reading data is) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 425.50 Tm (the simplest case - you test it just by visiting a URL in your browser. The other three, which) Tj ET
