BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 399.80 Tm (The pom dot xml - Project Object Model - is Maven's build file. It declares what your project) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 384.80 Tm (depends on and how it's built. A Spring Boot pom has three parts worth knowing. First, the parent:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 369.80 Tm (your project inherits from spring-boot-starter-parent, which provides all those tested, compatible) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 354.80 Tm (library versions, so you rarely specify a version yourself. Second, dependencies: this is where your) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 339.80 Tm (starters go - here, just the web starter. Third, the build plugin: the spring-boot-maven-plugin is) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 324.80 Tm (what packages everything into that single executable fat JAR we talked about. So the pom is) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 309.80 Tm (short, because the parent and the starters are doing the heavy lifting for you.) Tj ET
