BT /F2 9.50 Tf 0.040 0.340 0.780 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 754.00 Tm (SAY \(read aloud\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 738.00 Tm (Let's recap what you now know. Spring Boot is a layer on top of Spring that removes setup friction) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 723.00 Tm (through four things: auto-configuration, an embedded server, starter dependencies, and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 708.00 Tm (production-ready features. Its guiding philosophy is convention over configuration. A request flows) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 693.00 Tm (through the DispatcherServlet to a controller, then a service, then a repository, then the database -) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 678.00 Tm (separation of concerns. At-SpringBootApplication bundles three annotations and its run method) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 663.00 Tm (boots everything. Dependency injection and the IoC container mean the framework creates and) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 648.00 Tm (wires your objects, giving you loose coupling and testability. And REST models resources as) Tj ET
BT /F1 11.00 Tf 0.120 0.120 0.140 rg 1 0 0 1 72.00 633.00 Tm (URLs acted on by HTTP verbs. That's the foundation - everything else in the series builds on it.) Tj ET
